wmn4jnotation.noteobjects

Class Note

  • java.lang.Object
    • wmn4jnotation.noteobjects.Note
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Durational

    public class Note
extends Object
implements Durational
    Class that defines a note. This class is immutable. The NoteBuilder class can be used for creating Note objects. Notes have pitch, duration, articulations, and can be tied. A sequence of tied notes functions like a singly linked list where a previous note keeps track of the following tied note.
    Author:
    otsobjorklund

      • getTiedDuration

        public Duration getTiedDuration()
        Get the total duration of tied notes starting from the onset of this note. For example, if three quarter notes are tied together, then the tied duration of the first note is a dotted half note. For a note that is not tied to a following note this is equal to the note's duration.
        Returns:
        The total duration of consecutive tied notes starting from the onset of this Note.

      • getFollowingTiedNote

        public Optional<Note> getFollowingTiedNote()
        Returns:
        The following Note that this is tied to wrapped in an Optional. Returns empty Optional if this note is not tied to a following note.
